d ‘embodiment,’ in  the earlier  evolution  of language.  In  following this  lead,  we adapted  a previous experiment which had investigated the correspondence between certain perceptual features of events, and different  grammatical orders arising as participants  acted out those events. That design made a perfect basis for us to put in an additional variable, namely the contrast  between  body-based  communication  (gestures),  and  more  disembodied communication (symbol matching). Albeit tentative, the results of this pilot experiment reveal a greater effect of the embodiment variable on the grammatical preferences, which we see as inviting further exploration of embodied cognition in language evolution.","tags":["language evolution","linguistics"],"title":"Language evolution: current status and future directions","type":"publication"}]
